# from LFQ data by restructuring it and fitting growth curves to the restructured data (Pauly 1980). It is recommended to start by visualising the raw and restructured LFQ data, which aids in determining an appropriate bin size and the moving average of the restructuring procedure. The function lfqModify allows changing the bin size by setting the argument bin_size to a numeric value. The function lfqRestructure is used for the restructuring process, where the argument MA allows the control of the number of bins used for the moving average and the argument addl.sqrt allows for an additional square root transformation in the restructuring process, which reduces the weighting of large individuals.

